metadata.label: Title
value: Rupturs, their causes and varietie's : with various methods for curing them by applications both outward and inward, with the different kinds of trusses discribed together with the druags and simples, their places of growth and manner of preparing them

metadata.label: Alt Title
value: Ruptures, their various kinds, causes, and cure

metadata.label: Extent
value: 95 leaves : paper, illustrations ; 261 x 205 (211 x 160) mm bound to 271 x 207 mm

metadata.label: Note
value: Table of contents: 1. p.1-11:  Ruptures, their various kinds, causes, and cure.  -- 2. p.12-38:  Trusses, theire kinds and uses.  -- 3. p.40-47:  Of vegetables and manner of preparing them for the cure of ruptures in generall.
Pagination: Paper, 95; [viii], 1-2, 4-47, [48-179]; contemporary pagination in ink, modern pagination in pencil, upper outer corners.
Script: Written in a cursive script by a single hand, with notes and drawings on final leaves possibly in a second hand.
Decoration: Pen and ink and pencil drawings, primarily of trusses.
Binding: Contemporary leather, spine cracked, covers detached.
Origin: Possibly written in England in the second half of the 18th century .
One printed leaf laid in from the Philadelphia company Chesterman & Streeter, successors to I.B. Seeley & Co. is dated December 24, 1896 and titled "A word about trade protection."

metadata.label: Subject

metadata.label: Provenance
